title: Rainessa ASMR
description:
„ÉΩ(*ÔºæœâÔºæ*)Ôæâ Welcome Friend!

Thank you so much for stopping by!  

I hope you find this channel to be a spot of relaxation, calm & peace.

My goal is to share creativity, positivity & love to help you sleep comfortably & soundly!

Good night & sweet dreams, my friend!!!!! ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•

What is ASMR?
ASMR stands for autonomous sensory meridian response which is a biological reaction that some people may experience when they hear, see or feel certain satisfying triggers such as whispering, tapping, brushing or typing. It is best know for causing tingly sensations, relaxation and comfortable feelings.

Because of this, many people use ASMR as a way to help relax and sooth their mind and bodies before falling asleep. It can be used for meditation, sound therapy and is a natural sleep aid. I watch ASMR every night to fall asleep - and several times throughout the day as a part of my self care practice to keep my body, mind & spirit healthy and balanced! I love it!!!

description:
Hey friend! Welcome to my main channel Ozley ASMR (my only other channel is Ozley ASMR Shorts).  I am SO happy you decided to stop by! Grab your headphones for the full binaural experience, curl up with a cozy blanket, and stay awhile.

If you are new to ASMR, it stands for Autonomous Sensory Meridian Response, and it's a delightful tingly sensation some people get when experiencing certain sounds or visuals (tapping, rain, whispering, hand movements, just to name a few). Even if you don't experience "the tingles" these videos are perfect for relaxing, studying, and falling asleep. 

Have a browse through my collection of videos and don't forget to say hi before you go!

title: FrivolousFox ASMR
description:
Howdy ho hi B) I'm Frivvi. or Lauren. But Frivvi sounds cooler so we'll go with that. Welcome :')

After losing the love of my life due to a car accident (its complicated), I became depressed & reclusive. This channel served as an outlet for me to be *me.* To learn, grow, connect, & heal. For me, ASMR isn't just about tingles or relaxation. It's about feeling good. Smiling. Laughing. Connecting. Feeling a part of something bigger, but something REAL. I'm not the most professional or technically-polished ASMRtist, but that's okay! I think. Probably not. But if you extend a bit of patience, I'll prove that this channel & community is worth it. Or can be. Just gO WITH IT OK

Frivolous means light-hearted. Foxes are cool. ASMR isn't a medical alternative, but it's helped me in a way no therapist could. I whisper, I ramble, I tap, I kiss, I nom, I sing, I mess up, I giggle. I would LOVE for you to join me on this journey of self-acceptance, love, *MOUTH SOUNDS*, tingles & smiles.

AFFILIATE LINKS
E-Win Racing: https://bit.ly/3vfVQYl & 20% off promo code "theASMRnerd"
Into The AM: https://bit.ly/ASMRnerdINTOTHEAM

WHAT IS ASMR?
My videos are designed to trigger a relaxing feeling called ASMR (Autonomous Sensory Meridian Response). ASMR is a particular sensation that some people experience when they hear quiet sounds like whispering and soft speaking or watch certain actions like slow hand motions. ASMR is often described as a pleasant tingling on the head and neck, accompanied by a feeling of deep calm and mild euphoria. Many people watch ASMR videos to relax and manage anxiety, stress, or insomnia. To learn more about ASMR, check out https://asmruniversity.com/about-asmr/what-is-asmr.

title: ASMR Love by T
description:
Welcome to ASMR Love by T. I'm very happy you are here! Who am I? Someone that loves the tingly feeling from ASMR. 

I understand how difficult it is to find a sound that truly relaxes you, and normally, when you find it, it lasts a very short time or not enough time for you to really relax or fall asleep. That is why I concentrate on making long single trigger ASMR videos, although I also make long compilations of my best triggers, just so everyone can find what they need here. 

I'm very committed to help you all find that one ASMR sound that works for you, so do not hesitate to send me suggestions of what I should do next if I haven‚Äôt yet made your perfect ASMR video.

I thank you very much for visiting my channel and for your support. Big tingly hugs.

title: asmr zeitgeist
description:
ASMR Zeitgeist provides you with high-quality ASMR video content to help you sleep and relax. Tingles guaranteed! ;D

ASMR (–ê–°–ú–†, Èü≥„Éï„Çß„ÉÅ) stands for Autonomous Sensory Meridian Response and describes a pleasurable tingling sensation on the scalp or spine triggered by various stimuli.

These triggers might be sounds like soft whispering, crinkly plastic, tapping or scratching different materials and many more. 

The science behind this euphoric experience has to be further explored. Some reliable studies already suggest that it can be a powerful method to help people reduce depression, anxiety or insomnia. 

This YouTube channel is dedicated to the zeitgeist of ASMR. My goal is to offer all the popular triggers in optimal sound quality and to break new grounds with an open mind and creativity. I want you to have the best possible ASMR!

If you are seeking for some tingling relaxation, subscribe and hit the notification bell! :)

title: ASMR Jeremiah
description:
Welcome to my corner of the ASMR universe. 

Tingles, relaxation, connection, and deep, deep sleep. 

ASMR stands for autonomous sensory meridian response. It's the tingly sensation people get when they hear certain sounds. 

I've had trouble sleeping for the past several years and I want to help others get the deep sleep they deserve. 

Not every person gets the "tingles", but even non-tinglers can get a deep sense of relaxation and calm as they drift into peaceful slumber. 

Put on your headphones or earbuds to enjoy the 3D binaural soundscape, take a deep breath, and relax with me as we explore this amazing sensory world. 

With Warmth and Affection,
ASMR Jeremiah

title: JayLynn ASMR
description:
I am a Canadian ASMRtist who has been watching ASMR on a daily basis since 2014, but has experienced ASMR since I was a young child. I decided to create a YouTube channel to help others the way ASMR has helped me. 

ASMR has helped me through stress, inability to fall asleep, anxiety, panic, and depression. I know I cannot cure these for you, but my hope is that I can at the very least help you relax and make your day a little better. 

The main purpose of this channel is to relax you, and create a calming environment. It is a place of positivity, and to feel safe. Relax, and happy drifting, everyone!

I prefer fast ASMR triggers, so my pace is generally fast and focus mainly on tapping and scratching! :)

title: ASMR Peaches
description:
Welcome...
My channel, ASMR Peaches, is your retreat for relaxation and tingles guarantee! I provide you with high-quality ASMR videos to help you sleep or just relax.

ASMR means Autonomous Sensory Meridian Response and describes a pleasurable tingling sensation on the scalp or spine triggered by various stimuli. 
And exactly that triggers i create in my videos for you. These might be sounds you know from the barber shop (haircut), soft whispering or tapping/scratching on different materials. These sounds recorded with a special microphone will give you pure goosebumps and contentment.

Some reliable studies recommend ASMR to help people reduce anxiety, depression or insomnia. Just try it out and subscribe to my channel

I speak English, German and Russian

description:
ORIGINAL ASMR MUSIC PRODUCTION BY MATYO

Hey! I'm Matyo, welcome to my channel - place, where asmr meets music and rhythm. title: HunniBee ASMR
description:
Hello :)
This is an ASMR channel, which hopefully helps you either fall asleep or just feel relaxed ^__^
ASMR stands for autonomous sensory meridian response which can feel like a tingling sensation on the skin that usually starts at the scalp and moves down to the back of the neck and upper spine. (Got that definition from wikipedia lol it's not my own). But if you've ever had someone play with your hair or draw on your back, which I'm sure you have, you would have experienced this feeling!! (It is the bessstttt) So my goal on this channel is to give you those brain tinglezzz and help you sleep üò¥

Hi I'm Lisa, welcome to my ASMR channel. I'm so happy that you've found me :)
I upload every Mon, Wed, & Fri! 

What is ASMR? "ASMR stands for 'autonomous sensory meridian response'. People describe a deeply relaxing sensation with tingling in the scalp as a result of a certain stimulus‚Äîoften a gentle sound. Some say the feeling cascades down their spine to their limbs". ASMR is triggered by things such as whispering, softly speaking, tapping, personal attention, accents, and other various triggers. I personally enjoy ASMR as entertainment, for relaxation, to help with sleep, and also to manage stress. Many people also use ASMR for comfort, and to feel less alone as well, which is a wonderful feeling of community and belonging. I hope you all feel welcome here, and I hope to lull you into a state of relaxation, entertainment, or maybe even sleep through my ASMR videos.

Love, Lisa (LullingLisa ASMR)

title: ASMR Jeremiah
description:
Welcome to my corner of the ASMR universe. 

Tingles, relaxation, connection, and deep, deep sleep. 

ASMR stands for autonomous sensory meridian response. It's the tingly sensation people get when they hear certain sounds. 

I've had trouble sleeping for the past several years and I want to help others get the deep sleep they deserve. 

Not every person gets the "tingles", but even non-tinglers can get a deep sense of relaxation and calm as they drift into peaceful slumber. 

Put on your headphones or earbuds to enjoy the 3D binaural soundscape, take a deep breath, and relax with me as we explore this amazing sensory world. 

With Warmth and Affection,
ASMR Jeremiah

title: Hungry Herbivore ASMR
description:
Hello there!

Welcome to my ASMR eating sounds channel where I enjoy a variety of delicious vegan foods for your relaxation and viewing pleasure :) 

All meals are 100% plant-based. And I don't always finish my food...

Thank you so much for watching!

What is ASMR? Autonomous Sensory Meridian Response (ASMR) is a physical and pleasurable reaction to certain acoustic, visual and/or tactile stimuli. These soothing stimuli can evoke relaxation, sleepiness, body tingling, stress relief, euphoria, comfort, and a sense of calm in those who experience ASMR. Common triggers include repetitive sounds, personal attention, soft touch, whispering and hand movements.

title: AftynRose ASMR
description: Hi there! My name is Aftyn and thank you for visiting my channel! I make videos designed to help you relax, feel happy, or trigger what we call tingles throughout your body. ASMR stands for autonomous sensory meridian response and refers to a tingly, static like sensation due to the use of sounds and sometimes visuals- although I believe the visual trigger is referred to as AVRIC. In my videos I like to combine the two in hopes of creating a comforting experience for you. I try to be as open and myself as possible in the videos and I hope that you enjoy my personality, and the love that I wish to give. It is my dream to open your mind up to a new form of relaxation and to help you feel as loved and at ease with the current moment as possible. Anxiety, depression, and loneliness are some of the worst feelings to cope with and my hope with ASMR is to make those long lonely nights a bit easier on you. I hope you find something here for you and thanks again for checking out my channel!

Sometimes-weird 'inuntentional' ASMR and FPC videos to help you relax, unwind, and sleep. Often miswritten as Jim 5.

ASMR Community Guidelines: jimchicommunity.carrd.co

üéô What is ASMR? üéß

ASMR (autonomous sensory meridian response) is synaesthesia of the soul. It‚Äôs a relaxing feeling, it‚Äôs a tingling down the spine, or it‚Äôs simply a sleep aid. Whether it‚Äôs being ‚Äòheld‚Äô by someone you have confidence in, or ‚Äòlooked after‚Äô by someone with authority, or just feeling ‚Äòsafe‚Äô with someone you trust, it uses audio-visual triggers to enable you to let go of your worries.

üìΩ What is FPC? üéû

FPC (first person cinema) takes all the relaxing elements of ASMR but has much more of a focus on immersion and the suspension of disbelief. It‚Äôs kinda like being the main character in your own short movie, with popular figures you know and love, or entirely created worlds ‚Äì they are unique and relaxing experiences designed to transport you to different places, worlds, and times.

description:
Ciao, benvenut*!
Mi chiamo Fiorella e questo canale YouTube √® dedicato al relax, precisamente all'ASMR.

üî∏ASMR √® un acronimo che sta per Autonomous Sensory Meridian Response, in italiano "Risposta Autonoma del Meridiano Sensoriale". 
üî∏L'ASMR √® una forma di profondo rilassamento indotto da qualcosa che si sente o si vede, spesso accompagnato da un formicolio che parte dal cervello per scendere poi lungo la spina dorsale ed estendersi a tutto il corpo.
üî∏L'ASMR √® anche definito orgasmo cerebrale con il neologismo inglese "braingasm". Gli inneschi che fanno scaturire queste piacevoli sensazioni si chiamano "triggers" e possono essere uditivi (quindi rumori, sussurri, suoni particolari) e visuali (ad esempio il dolce movimento delle mani).
üî∏L'ASMR pu√≤ aiutare a combattere insonnia, ansia, panico, negativit√†. Chiaramente non si sostituisce a un supporto psicoterapeutico.

Hey! Welcome to my channel, I'm happy to see you here! This is an ASMR channel, so my goal is to relax you and make you feel confortable. I hope you'll enjoy the time spent here and feel free to come back whenever you want!

But...what is ASMR? 
ASMR is an acronym for ‚ÄúAutonomous Sensory Meridian Response", a physical sensation characterized by a pleasurable tingling that typically begins in the head and scalp, and often moves down the spine and through the limbs.
So, the sole purpose of ASMR videos is to relax and entertain the viewer. 
ASMR videos usually involve one or more of the following things:

‚Ä¢ Gentle whispering 
‚Ä¢ Relaxing hand movements 
‚Ä¢ Smacking of the lips 
‚Ä¢ Nail tapping/scratching on hard surfaces such as tables 
‚Ä¢ Brushing sounds

description:
Hi there! This is Mae!

I've been doing ASMR sessions for years now as a method of relaxing after long tiring days. Recently, my friend and I decided to start capturing it! As we became more involved in the community, we realized there are many more like us that receive relaxation and pleasure from ASMR massaging! We want to be a part of this community and share our passion with you as well!

We also have a large appreciation for feet and those who enjoy them as they are an underappreciated part of the body. We believe feet are beautiful and should be celebrated, this is why we have also created a foot-themed Instagram where we release creative and artistic photos of beautiful, local feet.

I am very grateful to share these videos with you because we enjoy making them and they are very helpful in getting better sleep and relaxation.

title: TOUCH MUSEUM ASMR
description:
Touch Museum is an ASMR YouTube channel and immersive video installation by visual artist Julie Weitz. The project explores the experience of embodiment in the digital realm through the sensory phenomenon known as Autonomous Sensory Meridian Response. 

The exhibition originally premiered  at Young Projects Gallery in Los Angeles from November 2015- February 2016 and is currently on view at Archer School for Girls in Los Angeles, CA through December 16, 2016. 

For more information visit www.julieweitz.com.

Hello!
My name is Ishino and I am from Japan.
I am a massage therapist in Tokyo, where I provide a safe space for people so they can relax and feel at ease. Through my massages, I want to show that everyone deserves to feel their best.
Nowadays, we are so incredibly busy that it is more important that ever to take good care of our body, mind and soul.

On Youtube, I want to take you on a journey of healing, self-care and relaxation. I would like to help you discover your body's natural healing power.

On my channel I will show you different massage techniques from all over the world. I will also share important knowledge and give you helpful advice so you can become the best and most relaxed version of yourself.

title: emptiness asmr
description:
"Emptiness‚Äù means empty of a separate self. It is full of everything, full of life. The word ‚Äúemptiness‚Äù should not scare us. It is a wonderful word. To be empty does not mean to be nonexistent. If the sheet of paper is not empty, how could the sunshine, the logger, and the forest come into it? How could it be a sheet of paper? The cup, in order to be empty, has to be there. Form, feelings, perceptions, mental formations, and consciousness, in order to be empty of a separate self, have to be there.

Emptiness is the ground of everything. ‚ÄúThanks to emptiness, everything is possible.‚Äù That is a declaration made by Nagarjuna, a Buddhist philosopher of the second century. Emptiness is quite an optimistic concept. If I am not empty, I cannot be here. And if you are not empty, you cannot be there. Because you are there, I can be here. This is the true meaning of emptiness. Form does not have a separate existence.

-Thich Nhat Hanh

title: Relaxing asmr with Flora
description: Peace. Tranquility. relaxation. These are words that come to mind when in the midst of nature. In the go-go-go culture we live in, those sensations can be hard to come by. Listening to nature sounds, such as this recording of a stream, can bring back that feeling of calm. This water sound has many different elements. Closest to the viewer/listener, you can hear the gentle sounds of water lapping. A little further back, you can hear the ambient noise of a stream. In the distance, you can hear the cascading sounds of water flowing over a small waterfall. And deep in the jungle, you hear the sounds of cicadas singing. ASMR, a feeling of well-being combined with a tingling sensation in the scalp and down the back of the neck, as experienced by some people in response to a specific gentle stimulus, often a particular sound Or Sounds.

title: Eddie Does ASMR
description:
Hey there! I'm Eddie from Canada! And I do ASMR videos mostly focused on...

- Roleplays
- Soft Spoken and Whispered Video Game Let's Plays
- History and Education
- Relaxing Sound Therapy

But primarily, I just wanna help you fall asleep :)

What the heck is ASMR? It stands for Autonomous Sensory Meridian Response... which really doesn't help explain what it is at all! 

Essentially, it's a relaxing tingling sensation some people get that starts in your scalp and can work it's way down your back. It's usually triggered by external stimuli such as when you go for a haircut, or have an eye exam, or watch someone concentrate on a task. I remember getting it as a child when my friends would trace letters and words on my back and I had to guess what they wrote.

Not everyone gets ASMR tingles, but the videos can be used for relaxation and to help shut your brain off at night.

Vlog Channel: http://goo.gl/yaUAJY

title: Bryoni ASMR
description:
Hey there, I'm Bryoni. 
ASMR is an abbreviation for Autonomous Sensory Meridian Response. It is a response or reaction to a certain sound, visual, or stimuli. ASMR can help individuals to reduce depression, insomnia, and anxiety. Alternatively, it can be used to help with relaxation for sleep and as a mechanism to help with studying. 

**DISCLAIMER** 
I create ASMR videos with the intention of helping people to relax, un-wind, and sleep. ASMR can be used as an aid to assist with relaxation, studying, and de-stressing. You should seek professional help if you are struggling with your mental health. ASMR is by no means a viable treatment. 

Here are some links that may help you: 
1) https://www.betterhelp.com 
2) https://www.nhs.uk/nhs-services/mental-health-services/ 

Thank you for all your support. Stay Safe!

For business inquiries, please email: bryoniburns22@gmail.com

description:

it stand for?
ASMR is the term for the sensation people get when they watch stimulating videos or take part in other activities ‚Äî usually ones that involve personal attention. Many people describe the feeling as ‚Äútingles‚Äù that run through the back of someone‚Äôs head and spine. Others say the feeling is deeply relaxing, and can even cause them to fall asleep.


How does it work?
How ASMR works varies greatly from person to person. Some ‚Äî perhaps most ‚Äî people don‚Äôt get it at all. And the science on ASMR is basically nonexistent, so our understanding of it is so far based on anecdotes from around the internet.

What is ASMR?

Autonomous sensory meridian response (ASMR), sometimes auto sensory meridian response, is a tingling sensation that typically begins on the scalp and moves down the back of the neck and upper spine. A pleasant form of paresthesia, it has been compared with auditory-tactile synesthesia and may overlap with frisson.

description:
You have found my performance arts channel, based around sound creation and appreciation.

Hi-Fi, Lo-Fi, Da-Da - it's all ASMR to me. I record vibrating air molecules and magically deliver them across the world into your thunksponge.

ASMR is "Autonomous Sensory Meridian Response" - a pseudoscientific term for a relaxing tingling feeling caused by certain trigger sounds.

To experience a full 3D sound-stage it's recommended to use open-back headphones in a quiet place.

This channel is a result of my studies with ASMR University and won me my Master's Degree for content creation in July 2016. Join me on this crazy rollercoaster :D

Channel launch 0 subscribers - 4th Jan 2016

100 subscribers -7th Nov 2016

500 subscribers - 16th Feb 2017

1000 subscribers - 13th Aug 2017

5000 subscribers - 20th May 2018

10,000 subscribers - 25th January 2021

Stay for the beans

title: Fighting Loneliness ASMR
description:
If you're looking for male soft-spoken ASMR content to help you relax and sleep, you've come to the right place.

ASMR, or Autonomous Sensory Meridian Response, is a phenomenon that is characterized by a tingling sensation in the scalp and neck. This sensation is often triggered by certain sights, sounds, or tactile sensations. ASMR has been shown to be beneficial for many people, as it can help to reduce stress and anxiety levels.

I would like to connect with you. I can share exclusive content with you and get to know you better through messages on Patreon. If you are interested in a custom ASMR video, please reach out with your request at patreon.com/fightingloneliness.
